  "subject": "Turnkey build-direction for agent-sdk v0.2, consolidating the two ratified decisions (autonomous-dispatch direction 2026-05-28 + Workflows-composition amendment 2026-05-29) into one current spec so a fresh implementer session can execute without reconciling two docs; Director prioritized this build 2026-05-29 ('Build agent-sdk v0.2') as the refinement most directly gating a public reveal; deliverables + locked design calls + three-tier enforcement + conformance tests + the empirical run_seat() demo definition + the one gating dependency (roledef URL-resolution contract) with its interim default",

  "sent": "2026-05-29T13:00:00-04:00",
  "action_required": true,

  "body": "Director prioritized the agent-sdk v0.2 build 2026-05-29 (answer to 'what do we have to do next?' = 'Build agent-sdk v0.2') as the refinement most directly gating a public reveal. This is implementer-execution; oagp-strategist (this seat) does not write the package (bounded-authority + seat scope). What this memo provides is the strategist-scope deliverable: a SINGLE current build-direction that reconciles the two ratified decisions, since the 2026-05-29 amendment re-scoped the 2026-05-28 direction (compose-with-Workflows rather than build dispatch plumbing) and an implementer should not have to merge two docs by hand. AUTHORITATIVE SOURCES (both on main, ratified-by-merge): decisions/proposal-agent-sdk-v0.2-autonomous-dispatch.md (three-tier model + 7-item build directive + 7 conformance tests) and decisions/proposal-agent-sdk-v0.2-amendment-workflows-composition-and-positioning.md (the re-scope). Where they conflict, the amendment wins. The consolidated, current spec is in the body §2-§6. NOT in scope for this memo: I am not making implementer design calls (language already Python per v0.1; framework, file layout, backend-selection mechanism are yours). I am stating WHAT must hold (the governance invariants + the conformance bar), not HOW to code it. Execution requires a staffed implementer session (Director triggers, as on 2026-05-24); this seat stands by for any pattern-shape clarifications the build surfaces.",
  "body_ref": "2026-05-29-1300--oagp-strategist--oagp-implementer--agent-sdk-v0.2-consolidated-build-direction.body.md",

